                        <item xml:id="e1">- Endleaves fols. 1, 172, 174 are fragments of an old 15th-cent. (?) Synaxarion, containing parts of commemorative notices for:&#xD;
 22 and 23 Ḫǝdār (Cosmas and Damian, Cornelius); 8 Tāḫśāś (Esi and Thecla, Samuel); 7 and 8 Tāḫśāś (Samuel, Barbara and Juliana, Mathew). &#xD;
- The first strophe of Text I-1 is repeated in the upper margin of <locus target="#13v">13v</locus>, in hand a.&#xD;
- Titles of most of the miracles of St Mary (Text I-4a) are written in the upper margin of the miracle's incipit page, in red.&#xD;
- Corrections are written over erasures: e.g., <locus target="#13ra">13ra</locus>b, 33rb, 48ra, 69rb, 90va, 93rb, 149rb, 157va, 165va, 171rb.&#xD;
- A note has been erased from <locus target="#9rb">9rb</locus>, below Additio 1.&#xD;
- Several lines have been erased from <locus target="#77rb">77rb</locus>.&#xD;
- Sketches for ornamental bands on <locus target="#21va">21va</locus>, 28rb, 34va, 49ra; probably in hand a.&#xD;
- Spaces for rubricated names of the donor are left unfilled throughout Text I-4b.&#xD;
- Crude drawings on <locus target="#173rv">173rv</locus>.</item>
